{{wikipedia|dab=stealth}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|stĕlth}}, {{IPA|/stɛlθ/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/stElT/}}
* {{rhymes|ɛlθ}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} the attribute or characteristic of acting in [[secrecy]], or in such a way that the actions are unnoticed or difficult to detect by others.
# {{context|archaic|countable|lang=en}} an act of secrecy, especially one involving [[thievery]]
#* '''1877''', George Hill, ''An Historical Account of the Plantation in Ulster at the Commencement of the Seventeenth Century'', M'Caw, Stevenson & Orr, page 352:
#*: [The King] thinks it fit[...] that restitution according to this order be made to the petitioners for '''stealths''' committed upon them last winter (273).

